nounced because Marvel wished to have a character that only appears in ''Avengers'' films.<ref name="WhedonDec2014" /> In April 2015, Ruffalo told [[Collider (website)|Collider]] that [[Universal Pictures|Universal]] holding the distribution rights to Hulk films may be an obstacle to releasing a future Hulk standalone film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/new-hulk-solo-movie-mark-ruffalo-says-universal-owns-the-rights/|title=Mark Ruffalo Reveals Universal Owns the Rights to Solo ''Hulk'' Movies|last=Goldberg|first=Matt|publisher=Collider|date=April 14, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928084154/http://collider.com/new-hulk-solo-movie-mark-ruffalo-says-universal-owns-the-rights/|archive-date= September 28, 2015|url-status= live|access-date=April 14, 2015}}</ref>

